.TH XMAN2PDF 1 "2026-05-15" "User Commands" "CLI-Improved Manual"
.SH NAME
xman2pdf \- compile raw roff manual pages into high-fidelity PDFs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xman2pdf
.I <path_to_manpage_file>
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBxman2pdf\fR is an automation utility that ingests a raw UNIX manual source 
file (\fBroff\fR format) and compiles it into a universally accessible 
PDF document. 
.PP
The tool automatically handles filename parsing, extracts the base utility name, 
ensures the destination directory exists, and invokes the system compiler layout 
engine to generate a pristine, cross-platform publication format matching classic 
UNIX manual conventions.
.SH INSTALLATION
Copy the script from the GitHub repository to your $PATH, typically /usr/local/bin.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
This script relies directly on the \fBgroff\fR document formatting system. 
It must be installed and available in the current environment's \fB$PATH\fR.
.TP
\fBChecking for Groff:\fR
You can verify its presence using your refined visibility tool:
.I which groff
.TP
\fBMacOS Installation:\fR
If missing on a Mac environment, install it via Homebrew:
.I brew install groff
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Returns 0 on successful compilation. Returns 1 if no input file is specified, 
or if the underlying \fBgroff\fR compiler encounters an execution error.
